Package: SDALGCP2
Title: Fast Spatially Discrete Approximation to Log-Gaussian Cox Processes for Aggregated Disease Count Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Olatunji", "Johnson", email = "teejaystatistics@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Emanuele", "Giorgi", role = "aut"),
    person("Peter", "Diggle", role = "aut"))
Description: A faster, modernised successor to the 'SDALGCP' package. Implements a
    spatially discrete approximation to a log-Gaussian Cox process model for
    spatially aggregated disease count data, estimated by Monte Carlo Maximum
    Likelihood as in Christensen (2004) <doi:10.1198/106186004X2525> and Johnson
    et al. (2019) <doi:10.1002/sim.8339>. Performance-critical steps (aggregated
    correlation assembly, MALA sampling, the Monte Carlo likelihood, and the
    Kronecker-structured spatio-temporal likelihood) are implemented in C++ via
    'RcppArmadillo'. Adds statistical extensions including a nugget term, general
    Matern smoothness, importance-sampling diagnostics and re-anchored MCML.
Depends: R (>= 4.2.0)
